freewnn (1.1.0+1.1.1-a016-1.potato.2) stable; urgency=high

  * Non Maintainer Upload
  * previous security fix has some bug in postinst
    potato's adduser doesn't have --disabled-login, so installation/upgrade
    would be failed on potato system (reported on debian-users@debian.or.jp)
  * symlink failed because potato version of freewnn doesn't have
    /usr/share/wnn directory. Fix it
  * potato doesn't have deluser, use userdel instead in postrm

 -- Fumitoshi UKAI <ukai@debian.or.jp>  Mon, 20 Aug 2001 16:28:19 +0900

